# Operational Constraints on Executing Migrations

## Timing
- Migrations should be executed during low-traffic periods to minimize disruption.

## Tooling
- Utilize Supabase migration tools for comprehensive management of schema changes.

## Deployment Risks
- Monitor application behavior post-deployment to identify any unforeseen issues related to new structures.

## Safety Strategies
- Implement thorough testing to validate the behavior of the application with new tables and constraints.